            Gaza ceasefire at impasse
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/qatar-us-egypt-ceasefire-talks-breakthrough.jpg"
          alt="Qatar, which is acting as a mediator, along with the US and Egypt, warned that more time was needed for a breakthrough"
        />

        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>
              Qatar, which is acting as a mediator, along with the US and Egypt,
              warned that more time was needed for a breakthrough. Credits:
              AFP</i
            >
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Despite recent optimism following the Israeli PM's meeting with
            Trump, ceasefire talks between Israel and Hamas
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-10-jul-25-spotlight-h1-1-have-stalled?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >have stalled</a
            >
            after three days of indirect talks. Hamas and Palestinian officials
            demand unrestricted aid entry via UN agencies and international
            organizations, and have offered to release 10 hostages.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            However, Israel rejected those conditions, insisting on using a
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-10-jul-25-spotlight-h1-2-current-aid-mechanism?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >current aid mechanism</a
            >
            supported by the US. Israel also refuses to commit to a complete
            withdrawal from the Gaza areas it reoccupied after March 18, further
            delaying negotiations. They estimate 50 hostages remain in Gaza,
            with around 20 believed to be alive, and insist no agreement should
            compromise Israeli security.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; filter: blur(5px)">
            The
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-10-jul-25-spotlight-h1-3-last-ceasefire-collapsed?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >last ceasefire collapsed</a
            >
            after Israel resumed its offensive on March 18, ending a brief
            pause. Talks are part of a broader attempt to end the 21-month-long
            Gaza war. The Trump administration, represented by envoy Steve
            Witkoff, is pushing hard for a 60-day truce agreement, but progress
            is slow. Qatar, the lead mediator, says more time is needed for a
            breakthrough.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
